## 2. The decision

### 2.1 In one sentence

> Invoke V2 runs the same streaming pipeline as `/stream`, and a subscriber called `A2AStreamCollector` turns the AG-UI event stream into an A2A Message.

No new state variables. No output-node templating. No per-node wiring. **If a workflow streams correctly, it invokes correctly.**

### 2.2 Call flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Client
    participant Controller as invokeV2()
    participant Service as execute()
    participant Adapter as streamExecutionObservable()
    participant Collector as A2AStreamCollector

    Client->>Controller: POST /v2/.../invoke
    Controller->>Service: execute(id, dto)
    Service->>Adapter: stream (streamMode: 'verbose')
    Adapter-->>Collector: AG-UI events (text, widgets, HITL, ...)
    Note over Collector: accumulates parts[] in order
    Adapter-->>Collector: RUN_FINISHED (output)
    Collector-->>Service: A2AMessage
    Service-->>Controller: A2AMessage
    Controller-->>Client: 200 OK (A2A JSON)
```

### 2.3 Why not the alternatives

| Option                            | Description                                                                                          | Outcome                                                                                                   |
| --------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **A. Stream-and-collect** Ō£ģ       | Reuse stream events; collector builds parts in-flight                                                | **Chosen**                                                                                                |
| **B. Template parsing**           | Builder writes `finalAnswer` on the output node with `{{variable}}` placeholders; transformer parses | Parallel code path; silent drops when a builder forgets a variable; fails G5 and G10                      |
| **C. `finalAnswer` accumulator**  | New flow variable appended to by every content-producing node during execution                       | **Implemented and removed.** Required modifying every emitter node, duplicated content already on `thread.messages` and in the event stream, grew state size, required per-node opt-out for guardrails/skills |

> **Note:** Three of the source documents (`a2a-invoke-response-proposal.md`, `invoke-api-approaches.md`, `invoke-v2-overview.md`) describe Option C as the winning approach. It was later removed. The header comment of `A2AStreamCollector.ts` preserves that history.

