## 3. What consumers see

### 3.1 Happy path

**Request**

```http
POST /v2/workflow-engine/wf-abc-123/invoke
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bpc": "BPC001",
  "environment": "DEV",
  "version": "1.0",
  "interface": {
    "inputs": { "message": "Show me my recent orders" }
  },
  "options": { "sessionId": "session-001" }
}
```

**Response**

```json
{
  "message_id": "msg_run_1709024400_abc123",
  "role": "agent",
  "parts": [
    { "text": "Here are your recent orders:" },
    {
      "data": {
        "preText": "Looking up order...",
        "template": "<OrderTracker orderId='12345' />",
        "postText": "Order found."
      },
      "media_type": "pv"
    },
    { "text": "Let me know if you need anything else." }
  ],
  "metadata": {
    "status": "COMPLETED",
    "runId": "run_1709024400_abc123",
    "sessionId": "session-001",
    "output": {
      "selectedAgentId": "wf-abc-123",
      "selectedAgentName": "Order Agent"
    }
  }
}
```

The client renders `parts` top to bottom ŌĆö `text ŌåÆ widget ŌåÆ text`, exactly as the agent produced them.

### 3.2 HITL interrupt

```json
{
  "message_id": "msg_run_xyz",
  "role": "agent",
  "parts": [
    { "text": "Please approve this refund before I continue." }
  ],
  "metadata": {
    "status": "INTERRUPTED",
    "runId": "run_xyz",
    "sessionId": "session-001",
    "output": {
      "interrupt": {
        "checkpointId": "...",
        "nodeId": "approval-node",
        "payload": { "message": "Please approve this refund before I continue." }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

To resume, the consumer calls the same `/v2/.../invoke` endpoint with `options.resume.metadata.checkpointId`. The service detects the resume, replays events from the checkpoint, and returns another A2A Message (completed, interrupted again, or failed).

### 3.3 Error

```json
{
  "message_id": "msg_error_1709024400",
  "role": "agent",
  "parts": [{ "text": "Input validation failed: message: Required" }],
  "metadata": {
    "status": "FAILED",
    "errorCode": "EXECUTION_ERROR",
    "runId": "run_error_1709024400",
    "sessionId": "session-001"
  }
}
```

Errors always look like A2A Messages ŌĆö same shape, different `status`.

