## 4. How it works

### 4.1 The `A2AMessage` type

Defined in `services/libs/shared/src/dtos/a2a/a2a.types.ts`.

```typescript
export interface A2APart {
  text?: string;
  data?: any;
  media_type?: string;   // "pv" | "a2ui" | future
  metadata?: Record<string, any>;
}

export interface A2AMessage {
  message_id: string;
  role: 'user' | 'agent';
  parts: A2APart[];
  metadata?: Record<string, any>;
}
```

Three kinds of parts appear in V2 responses:

| Kind        | Shape                                                                          | Emitted when                         |
| ----------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------ |
| Text        | `{ text: "..." }`                                                              | Agent/LLM node produces text         |
| PV widget   | `{ data: { preText, template, postText }, media_type: "pv" }`                  | A Partial-View tool runs             |
| A2UI widget | `{ data: { surfaceId, rendererType, payload, ... }, media_type: "a2ui" }`      | An A2UI-capable tool runs            |

### 4.2 The collector (`A2AStreamCollector`)

Located at `services/libs/agentic-engine/src/workflow-execution/A2AStreamCollector.ts`. It exposes one public method:

```typescript
A2AStreamCollector.collect(stream$, runId, sessionId): Promise<A2AMessage>
```

**Internal state held while the stream runs**

| State             | Purpose                                                                                 |
| ----------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `parts`           | The ordered output being built                                                          |
| `textBuffer`      | In-flight text between `TEXT_MESSAGE_START` and `TEXT_MESSAGE_END`                      |
| `pvBuffers`       | In-flight PV widgets, keyed by `toolCallId` so concurrent tools do not mix              |
| `hitlInterrupt`   | Latest `on_interrupt` payload, if any                                                   |

**Event handling**

| Event                        | Action                                                                                      |
| ---------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `TEXT_MESSAGE_CONTENT`       | Append `delta` to `textBuffer`                                                              |
| `TEXT_MESSAGE_END`           | Flush `textBuffer` as `{ text }`, reset                                                     |
| `CUSTOM / PV_PRE_RENDER`     | Open a new PV buffer for `toolCallId`                                                        |
| `CUSTOM / PV_TEMPLATE`       | Set `template` on the matching PV buffer                                                     |
| `CUSTOM / PV_POST_RENDER`    | Set `postText`, flush pending text first, then push PV part, delete buffer                   |
| `CUSTOM / A2UI_MESSAGE`      | Parse JSON, flush pending text, push A2UI part                                               |
| `CUSTOM / on_interrupt`      | Cache payload for metadata                                                                   |
| `RUN_FINISHED`               | Cache `result` for metadata construction                                                     |
| `RUN_ERROR`                  | Resolve immediately with an error A2A Message                                                |
| Anything else                | Ignored (`TOOL_CALL_*`, `STEP_*`, `STATE_*`, `REASONING_ENCRYPTED_VALUE`, ...)               |

> **Why text is flushed before a widget push** ŌĆö this is what preserves order. If the LLM says *"here you go:"* and then a tool fires, the text must land in `parts` before the widget.

**On stream `complete`**

1. Flush any leftover `textBuffer`.
2. Build `metadata` from `RUN_FINISHED.result.output` (strip the reserved `messages` key).
3. If an interrupt was captured ŌĆö set `metadata.status = 'INTERRUPTED'`, nest the payload under `metadata.output.interrupt`, push a text part with the interrupt message.
4. If `parts` is still empty ŌĆö fall back to the last AI message from `output.messages` as a single text part.
5. Resolve `{ message_id: 'msg_' + runId, role: 'agent', parts, metadata }`.

### 4.3 Metadata

Top-level fields the collector always sets:

| Key           | Values                                                                  |
| ------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `status`      | `"COMPLETED"` / `"FAILED"` / `"INTERRUPTED"`                            |
| `errorCode`   | String (only on failure)                                                |
| `runId`       | `run_{timestamp}_{random}`                                              |
| `sessionId`   | From the request, or auto-generated                                     |
| `output`      | Non-reserved output-node keys (omitted if empty)                        |

The only **reserved key** is `messages` (conversation history). Everything else on the output node ŌĆö `selectedAgentId`, `selectedAgentName`, user keys like `relatedQuestions` ŌĆö flows through to `metadata.output`.

### 4.4 Input validation (Start node)

The Start node (`services/libs/agentic-engine/src/nodes/StartNode.ts`) supports a JSON-Schema-flavoured config called `inputValidation`.

```json
{
  "inputValidation": {
    "properties": {
      "message":     { "type": "string", "minLength": 1 },
      "attachments": { "type": "array" },
      "count":       { "type": "number", "minimum": 1, "maximum": 100 }
    },
    "required": ["message"]
  }
}
```

At run start, `StartNode` builds a Zod schema from `properties` and runs `safeParse` on `interface.inputs`. On failure, it throws; the graph produces `RUN_ERROR`, and the collector surfaces a `FAILED` A2A Message with a human-readable issue list.

**Supported types and validators**

| Type      | Extra validators                               |
| --------- | ---------------------------------------------- |
| `string`  | `minLength`, `maxLength`, `pattern`, `enum`    |
| `number`  | `minimum`, `maximum`                           |
| `boolean` | ŌĆö                                              |
| `array`   | items are `z.any()`                             |
| `object`  | treated as `z.record(z.any())`                 |

If `inputValidation` is not configured, validation is skipped ŌĆö backward-compatible with existing workflows.

### 4.5 End-to-end code (V2 path)

**Controller** ŌĆö `workflow-engine.controller.ts`

```typescript
@Post(':id/invoke')
@Version('2')
@HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)
async invokeV2(
  @Param('id') id: string,
  @Body() request: InvokeApiRequestV1,
): Promise<A2AMessage> {
  try {
    if (!request.options) { /* defaults */ }
    if (!request.options.sessionId) {
      request.options.sessionId = uuidv4();
    }
    const dto = this.dtoAdapter.v1ToInternal(request);
    return await this.workflowEngine.execute(id, dto);
  } catch (error) {
    return A2AResponseTransformer.buildErrorMessage(
      error.message ?? 'An unexpected error occurred',
      `run_error_${Date.now()}`,
      request.options?.sessionId ?? 'unknown',
      'EXECUTION_ERROR',
    );
  }
}
```

**Service** ŌĆö `workflow-engine.service.ts`

```typescript
async execute(id: string, invokeRequest: InvokeRequestDto): Promise<A2AMessage> {
  this.request.headers['RuntimeToken'] = invokeRequest.options?.runtimeToken ?? '';
  const headers = this.request.headers as Record<string, string>;

  // HITL resume path omitted for brevity

  const { compiledGraph, processedSchema } = await this.createGraph(id, invokeRequest);
  const langfuseCallback = this.createLangfuseCallback(id, invokeRequest /* ... */);

  const sessionId = invokeRequest.options?.sessionId || 'default';
  const runId = `run_${Date.now()}_${Math.random().toString(36).substr(2, 9)}`;

  const adapterRequest = WorkflowExecutionHelper.buildGraphRequest(
    id,
    invokeRequest,
    interfaceInputs,
    headers,
    [langfuseCallback],
    this.buildRuntimeContextForRequest(id, invokeRequest /* ... */),
  );
  adapterRequest.config = { ...adapterRequest.config, streamMode: 'verbose' };

  const stream$ = this.adapter.streamExecutionObservable(compiledGraph, adapterRequest);
  const tapped$ = await this.wrapV2WithSessionCapture(id, invokeRequest, sessionId, stream$);
  return A2AStreamCollector.collect(tapped$, runId, sessionId);
}
```

Two points worth noting:

- **`streamMode: 'verbose'` is forced.** `minimal` mode would drop PV widgets; whatever the caller passed is overridden.
- **`wrapV2WithSessionCapture`** taps the stream for session capture (same mechanism as streaming), then the collector subscribes to the tapped observable.
- **Runtime headers** ŌĆö `this.request.headers` (including `RuntimeToken`) are passed into `buildRuntimeContextForRequest(...)`, so tools that need header-based auth forwarding behave the same as on the stream path.

### 4.6 HITL resume

Same `/v2/.../invoke` endpoint. The caller sets `options.resume.metadata.checkpointId`. The service detects it, calls `handleResume(id, request, headers)` (shared with the stream path), unwraps the emitted `{ data, type }` events into raw AG-UI events, and feeds them into `A2AStreamCollector.collect(...)`. Resume responses return the same A2A shape ŌĆö completed, interrupted again, or failed.

### 4.7 Three versions coexist

| Version     | Endpoint                              | Returns                          |
| ----------- | ------------------------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| V0 (default) | `POST /workflow-engine/:id/invoke`    | `GepReturnDto` ŌĆö unchanged       |
| V1           | `POST /v1/workflow-engine/:id/invoke` | `GepReturnDto` ŌĆö unchanged       |
| **V2**       | `POST /v2/workflow-engine/:id/invoke` | **`A2AMessage`** ŌĆö this ADR      |

V0/V1 stay live until internal consumers migrate. Deprecation will be a separate ADR.

