## 7. Risks and trade-offs

| Risk                                                                      | Impact         | Mitigation                                                                                             |
| ------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| Invoke runs the full streaming pipeline even without a client             | Minor overhead | Acceptable ŌĆö dominated by LLM latency. A separate code path would drift from stream.                   |
| Nodes that only update state (no events) are invisible to invoke          | Silent content loss | Document in builder guidance. Require `TEXT_MESSAGE_*` / `CUSTOM` emission to appear in `parts[]`.  |
| Three invoke versions coexist                                             | Maintenance   | V0/V1 are frozen; deprecation tracked separately.                                                      |
| Legacy `A2AResponseTransformer` is dead code in the success path          | Reuse risk    | Header comment on `A2AStreamCollector.ts` documents the supersession. Cleanup tracked as tech debt.    |
| AG-UI event shapes change underneath us                                   | Collector breaks | Unit tests on the collector with representative event fixtures.                                     |
| V0/V1 consumers assume `messages` is in the response                      | Migration     | Called out in the Endpoints panel and in V0 ŌåÆ V2 migration notes.                                      |

